      "title": "",
      "text": "Hello everyone. My name is Jyoti and I'm a PhD scholar in HSS department at IIT Kanpur. I work in the area of AI ethics and particularly in bias and fairness in machine learning algorithms. For my PhD work, it is crucial for me to learn how a AI ML model works, how it is built and to have a hands on experience on how to build a machine learning algorithm for. For these reasons I enrolled in the AIML course offered by Visura and I'm glad I did. I could not have been in a better place. We have finished AIML Foundations for Machine Learning that covers mathematics required for it and for any serious machine learning enthusiast it is essential to cover the mathematical foundations behind it. As I gear up for the next module, I want to share some of the best things which I also feel are unique to the way teaching is done at Visura. To begin with, we are being taught by the best in the industry. Dr. Sridhutt would teach complex topics in AI ML in a very simple and simplified manner. He would use no jargons or big words that we cannot fathom. So for instance, if you are learning something in linear algebra or something in probability, he would do the math, draw the graph and actually show us how it is helpful or how it is related to a specific area in machine learning. Also, the usage of graph was particularly very helpful for me because I realized that when you use a graph to explain any kind of concept or to do some kind of problem solving, it simplifies a lot of complex things that we do not at first understand. It makes everything very understandable to us. So yeah, so these were some of the very attractive points for me as I began learning in this course. Apart from that they would not use the traditional PPT but a Miro board. So this was also my first experience to learn from a mirror board. So what the instructor would do is that whatever was required to be taught that day, he would have everything on the mirror board in a very cohesive manner. And whenever you would have doubt or there was something he wanted to explain deeply, he would move the mirror board to a blank space. He would move to a blank space in the mirror board and explain it using graphs, doing some maths. And he would also incorporate our ideas while explaining the topics to us, which also made us like felt inclusive because it was not something like that. We were only consuming from the instructor, whatever. If we had some idea, the instructor would put that on Miro board and we would try to work it out together to see the strength and the weakness of that particular idea. Apart from this, the assignments and tests were also given on time. They were timely assignments and tests which was also designed in a very creative manner. So folks at Visura strongly believe that we learn a lot by teaching. So we were given assignments to create a video where we had to explain the topics that we were working on as if we were explaining to some five year old and we were briefed as how we should be speaking or you know, it was not that we were just given the assignments to complete and there was a due date. We were actually briefed about it properly as how it would help us to do better at our assignments. Apart from that, we also tried writing a paper using latex tool. So in future as I advance in my knowledge or in my career in AI ML, I would want to publish paper. And for that I was happy that I was introduced to the latex tool which is essential to write any technical paper. Apart from that, we were also encouraged to have a healthy discussion about topics, brainstorm with our peers and we often found ourselves in breakout rooms. We also have a strong peer support in Discord. We can always write to instructor or ask him for any questions or clarifications in Discord itself. So the fact that all these classes were conducted virtually, we never felt like a hassle or a problem. It always felt like we were well connected and all of this was happening in a classroom. What I have mentioned are only few points to really understand how it works or to really leverage what is being provided in order to benefit oneself. You have to be here to see how it is being taught. I am very happy that I chose this course and I'm really excited to what comes next. Thank you so much.",
