      "title": "This Course Removed My Fear of Understanding Large Language Models",
      "text": "My biggest takeaway from this course was understanding the journey of how large language models (LLMs) evolved - from the early days of simple rule-based systems like the ELIZA chatbot, to basic neural networks, to the introduction of complex architectures like transformers, and finally to the modern-day LLMs we use today. This historical perspective made me appreciate the beauty and depth of the subject. More importantly, it helped remove the fear I had that LLMs were too difficult to understand. By breaking things down step by step, the course made these advanced concepts feel much easy to understand, and I was able to connect those topics to each other well enough. This course was absolutely amazing in every aspect. I especially appreciated the way Dr. Raj structured the notes: they were incredibly well-organized, conceptually clear, and made it easy to retain everything after watching the lectures. The use of the Miro board was a great touch, with embedded GIFs and videos that made the concepts even more engaging and easier to grasp. The teaching style was thoughtful and rooted in first principles, and the practical coding approach alongside each topic really solidified my understanding. The assignments were challenging and rewarding, though I felt the exams could be slightly tougher to match the depth of the course. Overall, it was a top-tier learning experience.",
