      "type": "text",
      "title": "One of the best teachers in the world",
      "text": "My biggest takeaway from this course was finally understanding how Large Language Models (LLMs) actually work under the hood. I started the course with a lot of curiosity—wondering how LLMs generate answers and what really goes on behind the scenes. Through this course, I learned that at the core, an LLM is simply predicting the next token based on probability, and everything else builds on top of that simple idea. This insight was eye-opening, and it helped me appreciate the elegance of the architecture. Along the way, I learned a wide range of foundational concepts that power LLMs—from tokenization (like byte pair encoding) to attention mechanisms, multi-head attention, loss functions, and training dynamics. The course didn’t just explain how LLMs work—it built the knowledge step-by-step, making sure every concept was deeply understood. Overall, it was an incredibly enriching experience that satisfied my curiosity and gave me a strong technical foundation. The course was very well organised and the notes was very crucial in this course and the recording lecture helps to grasp the concept more clearly , your teaching style was so nice to take the concept from very basic to advanced , the notes were also so much engaging to go through after the lecture, you teach the concept in a very gentle manner that it makes the concept clear and also answering each of the doubt during the lecture , that we also got to know the new insight of the problem, the whole course was so nice from tokenization to understanding the whole architecture of LLM, the way you calmly explain the concept it takes to different level, I think the world needs more teachers like you.",
