      "text": "Hi, my name is Tanush Salyan and I've had the privilege of being the part of the generative AI and build your own GPT from scratch course of Visura AI Labs. The course began with the absolute basics explaining us how AI and LLM models are impactful in our day to day lives. What stood out to me was how thoughtful and in a structural way the course was conducted. Our course instructor, Dr. Rajat Dandekar sir, made sure that we understood every concept of it. How it exactly started was with some fun group assignments where we were divided into groups and we were given some concepts we had to work on, we had to make a documentation on it and this pushed our scope beyond what was just taught to us in the lecture. So he always wanted us to explore out, to look out for more models and share with him the knowledge we have gained through it. What exactly helped us was how since this topic was not easy, there were complex models, complex architecture, which was very confusing in the beginning. But the way he taught us was first he covered all the theoretical concepts where, what are these layers, what are the models being used, why are the models being used, what are the concepts and the key parameters used within the models. And then he, he moved on to the coding approach of it. This made our understanding extremely easier and better because we already had the idea that what this function means and what exactly is going to happen within this function block. So the coding part as well as the theoretical part, both were going together and that made this course extremely interesting as well. So in the end, the part where we gained most of our knowledge after the course is the home assignments which were design in such a way that it was something where we had to work on our understanding, we had to explore more, we had to research more, we were given certain models, we were given certain data sets which we had to work on and get the result. And it was not only about the result. We had to tweak the parameters, we had to change some functions within the models so that we could observe and we could note down that how certain parameters affect and how does the AI model perform within certain situations. So I am sharing this to you to convey that how this transformative learning has been implied on me and I'm extremely grateful for this learning experience, thank you so much.",
