      "text": "I had been the student of Raj for two courses, the Generative AI Fundamentals and also the Building LLM from Scratch. Personally, this journey was absolutely enlightening for me because of very unique pedagogy that Raj follows in his teaching style. First is his approach is absolutely no nonsense. He goes to the details of a working code and explains everybody on how actually the entire concept is working on grassroots. But at the same time, he has this beautiful ability to actually abstract things whenever required because these concepts are so complex and so deep that it's very easy to lose the track. And you know, as Raj says, you will, you know, it's very easy to, you know, lose the perspective of the forest and get lost in the trees. And that is something that I feel is absolutely precious that he provides and providing that needed abstraction wherever required. He also explains and gives the confidence to all of us how actually to build things really from scratch. Another important thing that I found in the course was his focus on writing notes, handwritten notes, right? I mean, truly speaking, it has been, you know, decades I had made handwritten notes. And I really, really cherish that experience of writing handwritten notes for these concepts. And that I saw really, really increases the depth of my understanding. The third thing that he does is the assignments that he gives. They are good combination of actual coding assignments as well as teaching assignments. So we had to really record our videos teaching some important concepts and starting from scratch and make others understand that concept. So that is something that is, you know, class apart because it is only when you try to make somebody understand, you come out of those biases and those illusions that you might have that you have really understood, but only when you are trying to explain it to somebody, teach somebody those, you know, illusions and those shortcomings surface out. And I remember I had to really, really, you know, rework multiple times to have my sessions recorded. So this, these are the few key things that I think is actually not available in other platforms that I have seen which are providing the education for AIML and Generative AI at this point of time. So I really, really appreciate, you know, Raj and I would also like to mention that he gives enough time for us to really go deep into the concepts and understand by our own, right? I mean, take our own data sets and data says that we ourselves are connected more. Right. And I, I remember I, I really, you know, trained one SLM with Julius Scissor, which was like a school time nostalgia. It doesn't really make sense to train an SLM for Julius. But then it was just a wacky experiment that I did and he encouraged. And in that entire journey, I really understood a lot of things that were not, you know, present to me in this entire process. So a great hands on experience, lot of practical sessions, and above all, you know, a lot of focus on understanding and building things from scratch. So thanks a lot, Raj, for taking this initiative and really, really helping the community to have some meaningful depth in this area. Thanks again.",
