      "text": "Hi everyone, my name is Sanika Apte and I am currently in Germany after completing my studies here and I'm doing my job here. So I was a part of two classes from Vajoara and one being the MLDL Mastery and the second being Genai Fundamentals. So how I came to this is because I learned About Vajra from LinkedIn feed from LinkedIn post and they were going to organize a webinar on how to transition to aiml. So I joined that. I really found them very vibrant, very interesting and so I started watching their YouTube videos on how to go about with AIML. So the videos from Dr. Raj were really great. They were very nice and full of knowledge. Then I decided that yes, I really want to join the online courses and it was one of the best decisions that I made. I can definitely say this now. And regarding the lectures, what I felt was really cool was the that no concepts or nothing was assumed from before. Everything was taught from scratch. Everything was, you know, it's like, it's like taught in a way that you understand it in the best possible manner even if you are a beginner in this whole world of aiml. So yeah, the way these concepts are taught is the best thing that I liked about it. Also the interactions that we used to have with Dr. Raj during both of these courses was really good, was really nice. So if any one of you wants to transition to AIML from what you are doing currently then I would also recommend joining one of the courses from Visuara maybe next semester because they take into consideration that you are a beginner and also they do not assume anything. They teach you everything from the basics, from very first principles. So that is very important in building a great foundation for AIML when you that maybe want to work on it in your future. So highly recommended and a big thank you to Dr. Raj for his time for sharing his knowledge with all of us and also a big thank you to Vijayara for arranging these courses and making this content available to all of us. Thank you.",
